1
00:00:04,487 --> 00:00:06,202
That’s what 
we’re searching for—

2
00:00:06,202 --> 00:00:08,643
the imperfect 
is searching for the Perfect.

3
00:00:08,773 --> 00:00:12,443
[What do We Live For]

4
00:00:12,804 --> 00:00:15,114
We’re searching 
for the Ideal.

5
00:00:15,114 --> 00:00:17,210
We’re searching 
for the Absolute.

6
00:00:17,210 --> 00:00:18,810
That is what
life is.

7
00:00:18,810 --> 00:00:21,790
That is what 
existence is actually.

8
00:00:22,230 --> 00:00:28,953
It’s not a religion, 
a religious thing, a religious idea.

9
00:00:28,953 --> 00:00:30,677
It’s Reality.

10
00:00:31,447 --> 00:00:32,987
As once Guru Mahārāj said,

11
00:00:32,987 --> 00:00:35,328
“Kṛṣṇa consciousness is Reality,

12
00:00:35,328 --> 00:00:36,888
and it’s in your interest

13
00:00:36,888 --> 00:00:39,642
to become acquainted 
with this Reality.”

14
00:00:39,642 --> 00:00:43,012
It’s not Hinduism 
or an Indian religion,

15
00:00:43,012 --> 00:00:46,172
or something a particular group
of people believe.

16
00:00:46,172 --> 00:00:47,333
It’s Reality.

17
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:51,357
We have to start thinking 
of it that way.

18
00:00:52,054 --> 00:00:53,773
Therefore he used 
that expression:

19
00:00:53,773 --> 00:00:56,363
“Reality the Beautiful.”

20
00:00:56,363 --> 00:00:59,086
“Search for Śrī Kṛṣṇa,
Reality the Beautiful.”

21
00:00:59,086 --> 00:01:02,276
“The Ultimate Reality is beautiful.”

